reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 16, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Looks good and works... but needs a heavier base.
reviews.reviewText: I bought this as a desk lamp, which maybe wasn't the best idea because it creates a very diffuse light and isn't all that helpful if you need to read or write something. You can see that in the pics so I'm not holding it against it in this review - I'm reviewing it more as a bedside lamp, which seems more what it's more intended for. That said, the item title does list it as a desk lamp too.The lamp comes in a small box with a few separate parts but it was easy to put together. It came with a tiny, pretty dim light bulb - if you use an LED bulb, then you can put in a much brighter one yourself. There is a limit to the wattage but it's pretty high for LED bulbs and you'd never have to worry about it. (I don't remember the exact limit; way higher than any standard consumer LED bulb, though.)The USB and power ports all seem to work fine. I've used them to charge various things. It's also a nice size for a desk or bedside table and looks like something you'd see in a hotel.The one major annoyance is how light the base is. Especially when plugging or unplugging things, it just slides around all over the place. This seems to be a really common problem with a lot of stuff from these smaller Asian brands these days... I'm sure it has to do with shipping costs, trying to make their products as light as possible to save money on that. But it just makes it really annoying to plug things into and out of, and that's one of the lamp's main selling points, all the plugs on it. (It also just makes stuff feel cheap when it's this light, but that's a more minor point.)I'm sure the interior is mostly empty air so I will probably see at some point if I can open it up and just put some metal weights inside it. It also could use some grippier feet.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I like this lamp a lot more than I thought I would like it. It's very easy to turn on and off with the little button on the top. It's small, so doesn't take up a lot of space and I love the build in charger ports. It says that it has three ports, but the third one isn't a standard usb one, so I actually can only use two of the ports. I need three (kindle, phone, smart watch). Luckily there is also a build in outlet, so I've put a usb charger plug into that one. This has replaced the charger ports I had on my nightstand, so everything looks better and more efficient now. I'm overal really happy with this product.
